                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/14287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-27T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1918—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 28—11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1418. Your 786, August 15th, Foreign Office communicated with in sense of
                    Department’s 180, July 12th, and am now in receipt of reply as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows summary of British note of August 24, 1918, transmitted in despatch
                    no. 9821, September 3, from the Ambassador in Great Britain, <hi rend="italic"
                        >infra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Have transmitted copy of note and list to Skinner advising him to await
                    instructions from Department as to whether he should communicate with Procurator
                    General. Copy of Foreign Office note and full list to be forwarded by next bag.
                    Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
